==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blackwash
<hw>Black"wash</hw> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A lotion made by mixing calomel and lime water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A wash that blackens, as opposed to
<contr>whitewash</contr>; hence, figuratively, calumny.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To remove as far as he can the modern layers of <qex>black
wash</qex>, and let the man himself, fair or foul, be seen.</q>
<rj><qau>C. Kingsley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>blackwash</ent>⟦br⟧

